<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Activist vs. activist</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Traditionally activist hedge funds are=
, uh, hedge funds. They are privately managed pools of capital in which the=
 investors =E2=80=94=C2=A0the limited partners =E2=80=94=C2=A0do not get mu=
ch in the way of voting rights. If the investors in an activist fund do not=
 approve of its activism, they can (probably, eventually) withdraw their mo=
ney and invest it somewhere else, but they can=E2=80=99t, like, vote out th=
e hedge fund=E2=80=99s manager and install someone else. Activist hedge fun=
ds are not generally themselves susceptible to activism.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">In theory you could run an activist strategy out of, say, a m=
utual fund run by a publicly traded asset manager. But then someone might d=
o an activism on you: try to replace you as manager of the fund, mount a ho=
stile takeover of your asset-management firm, whatever. This would be embar=
rassing for you.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, i=
f you run a hedge fund, your most important <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/28141627.276598/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDMtMDQvbWVsdmluLWNhcGl0YWwtaW1wcm92ZXMtZnJv=
bS1nYW1lc3RvcC1yZWRkaXQtc3RydWdnbGU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYyMjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXR=
tX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNjIyJnV0bV=
9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB642acb70" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> goal=
</a> is to continue to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/28141627.276598/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMTgtMDctMDUvaXQtcy1iZXR0ZXItdG8tYmUtcmljaC10aGFuLXJpZ2h0P2NtcGlkPUJCR=
DA2MjIyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVy=
JnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYyMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB9fb5b712" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> run a hedge fund</a>. One way to do that is by sett=
ing up a permanent capital vehicle: Do some sort of offering of some sort o=
f entity whose shareholders=C2=A0<em>can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>just get their=
 money back, so that you have capital to invest even if investors lose fait=
h in you. Often this entails listing the entity publicly and giving it some=
 voting rights. This can be trouble.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28141627.276598/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvNWFiNmYzZTQtYjJlNi00MjA0LTg0NjAtNzZhNWYwMTg4Y2Y=
3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0ef7ae12" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Nelson Peltz has some activist=
s</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A London-listed fund lin=
ked to Nelson Peltz=E2=80=99s Trian Fund Management has come under pressure=
 from a group of insurgent investors seeking to shake up its board =E2=80=
=9Cto improve governance and restore trust=E2=80=9D.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">Peltz, known for waging campaigns against the management of compa=
nies including consumer goods group Unilever and asset manager Janus Hender=
son, has found himself the target of investors demanding changes at his Tri=
an Investors 1 fund.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A committee of investo=
rs =E2=80=94 made up of asset managers Global Value Fund, Invesco, Janus He=
nderson Investors UK Limited and hedge fund Pelham Capital =E2=80=94 has se=
rved notice to convene an extraordinary general meeting of its shareholders=
.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Trian Investors 1 was not ex=
actly supposed to be a permanent capital vehicle but:</p><blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Trian Investors 1 was listed in September 2018 =
it set out to invest into a single publicly listed target, work to improve =
the business and then exit the investment and return capital to shareholder=
s. This model is similar to that employed by Edward Bramson=E2=80=99s activ=
ist vehicle, Sherborne Investors.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">However, =
last year, ahead of its AGM, the board of Trian Fund 1 proposed a series of=
 changes to the investment policy that the committee believes would financi=
ally benefit the manager. Crucially, these changes would=C2=A0allow it to o=
wn multiple=C2=A0investments simultaneously, and instead=C2=A0of returning =
all capital and profits to shareholders=C2=A0after exiting an investment, t=
he manager could reinvest them.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">The classic activist move is to demand that corporate managers return cap=
ital to shareholders, while the managers say =E2=80=9Cno we have a long-ter=
m plan to enhance shareholder value and would like to use that capital ours=
elves, trust us.=E2=80=9D The applications to fund management are obvious. =
Also:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The participation of the =
Janus Henderson fund in the activist group puts the US asset manager in a d=
elicate position since Peltz has been pushing for sweeping changes at the c=
ompany and in February won a seat on its board.</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Trian is activisting Janus, and Janus is activisting Tria=
n. The future of activist investing might be all the activists activisting =
each other.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto"=
