=E2=80=99s future, the post lit a fire.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The=
 proposal from Honey Barrel=E2=80=94an average, albeit vocal member of the =
organization=E2=80=94threatens to usher in a new, distinctly investor-unfri=
endly era in the DAO world. Because if one DAO breaks its legal contract wi=
th an investor, what=E2=80=99s to stop others from doing the same? For vent=
ure capital firms that have put millions into DAOs=E2=80=94including giants=
 such as Andreessen Horowitz, Union Square Ventures, Sequoia Capital and Pa=
radigm=E2=80=94the ripple effects could be existential.</p></blockquote><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The proposal passed. The DAO voted to kick one Me=
rit Circle investor =E2=80=94=C2=A0Yield Guild Games =E2=80=94=C2=A0out of =
the DAO. YGG had bought its tokens from Merit Circle Ltd. (the legal entity=
 connected to the DAO) for about $0.03 each; they were trading at about $1 =
at the time of the proposal. Merit Circle=E2=80=99s management team, who pr=
esumably understood that =E2=80=9Crefund money to investors who aren=E2=80=
