</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Egan-Jones Ratings Co. is a ratings ag=
ency that gives credit ratings to debt deals. The way credit ratings genera=
lly work is that an issuer comes to the ratings agency and asks for a ratin=
g, the agency considers the deal and gives it a rating, and the issuer pays=
 the agency for the rating. This creates some obvious conflicts of interest=
 that are mostly regulated in=C2=A0obvious ways. The US Securities and Exch=
ange Commission <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28=
141627.276598/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4xN=
2ctNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB66c9d1e7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">rules require</a>, for i=
nstance, that the ratings-agency employees who solicit issuers for business=
, manage their relationships and collect the fees have to be separate=C2=A0=
from the employees who do the ratings. And there has to be enough process a=
nd documentation that the agency can say =E2=80=9Cwe gave this AAA rating b=
ecause it was justified by the credit, not because they paid us a lot of mo=
ney.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In practice this separa=
tion seems hard, or at least=C2=A0<em>awkward</em>, to enforce. You can=E2=
=80=99t really have a rating agency where the person giving the rating does=
n=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>talk=C2=A0</em>to the issuer: You need to talk to the =
issuer to understand the thing that you are rating. If you talk to the issu=
er about the deal, and then you say =E2=80=9Cokay I=E2=80=99m giving you a =
BBB+ rating,=E2=80=9D and the issuer says =E2=80=9Cthat=E2=80=99s ridiculou=
s, it should be A+ at least, I will never use your ratings agency again, ki=
ss those fees goodbye,=E2=80=9D you=C2=A0<em>can=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0a=
rguably you=C2=A0<em>should=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0reply =E2=80=9Cthat is=
 none of my concern, good day sir,=E2=80=9D but that isn=E2=80=99t easy. Yo=
u do get paid out of those fees, after all.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Egan-Jones, and its founder and chief executive officer Sean Egan,=C2=A0<a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28141627.276598/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMi0xMTE/607f07ceef4b852=
